SQL Query:
SELECT DISTINCT mp."company_name",
    avg(ep1."close") AS avg_10_day,
    avg(ep2."close") AS avg_20_day,
    avg(ep3."close") AS avg_30_day,
    avg(ep6."close") AS avg_6_month
FROM "master_prime_1d" mp
JOIN "equity_prices_1d" ep1 
    ON mp.security_code = ep1.security_code
JOIN "equity_prices_1d" ep2 
    ON mp.security_code = ep2.security_code
JOIN "equity_prices_1d" ep3 
    ON mp.security_code = ep3.security_code
JOIN "equity_prices_1d" ep6 
    ON mp.security_code = ep6.security_code
WHERE ep1."date_time" BETWEEN '2024-10-29' AND '2024-11-19'
    AND ep2."date_time" BETWEEN '2024-10-19' AND '2024-11-19'
    AND ep3."date_time" BETWEEN '2024-10-09' AND '2024-11-19'
    AND ep6."date_time" BETWEEN '2024-05-19' AND '2024-11-19'
    AND (
        (ep1."close" > (SELECT "close" FROM "equity_prices_1d" WHERE "date_time" = '2024-10-20' AND "security_code" = ep1."security_code"))
        AND (ep2."close" > (SELECT "close" FROM "equity_prices_1d" WHERE "date_time" = '2024-10-13' AND "security_code" = ep2."security_code"))
        AND (ep3."close" > (SELECT "close" FROM "equity_prices_1d" WHERE "date_time" = '2024-10-06' AND "security_code" = ep3."security_code"))
    )
GROUP BY mp."company_name"
HAVING count(DISTINCT ep1."date_time") = 10
    AND count(DISTINCT ep2."date_time") = 20
    AND count(DISTINCT ep3."date_time") = 30
    AND count(DISTINCT ep6."date_time") >= 126;
